Sentencas: Variants of SNNV (Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3, X = 0.1-03) ceramic oxides were synthesized via wet chemical method.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: SNNVs show high electronic conductivity of > 100 S/cm when reduced in hydrogen at a relatively low temperature of 650 degrees C.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In particular, 30% V-doped SNNV exhibited the highest conductivity of 300 S/cm at 450 degrees C.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In order to investigate the fuel cell performance, Gd0.1Ce0.9O2-delta (GDC) based electrolyte-supported fuel cells were prepared to study the anode characteristics.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Sr0.2Na0.8Nb0.9V0.1O3 (SNNV10)-GDC composite was used as an anode and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF)-GDC as a cathode.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Both electrodes were porous and sintered at 1050 degrees C for 2 h in air.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The anode side of the fuel cell was infiltrated with 10 wt% GDC/Ni-GDC precursor to activate the anode for fuel oxidation.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: I-V characteristics were determined in gas conditions such as dry/humidified hydrogen and methane at 650 degrees C. With the infiltration Ni-GDC, peak power density (PPD) of 280 mW/cm(2) and 220 mW/cm(2) in dry H-2 and CH4, respectively, were obtained at 650 degrees C, which is higher than GDC alone as infiltrate.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The high resistances in the humidified conditions are attributed to the lower conductivity of SNNV10 in high P-O2 atmospheres.
Titulo: Investigation on Sr0.2Na0.8Nb1-xVxO3 (x=0.1, 0.2, 0.3) as new ceramic anode materials for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
